One way of looking at this is that the changes from &quot;plain&quot; vector to column vector and back are assumed and left implicit.

===Vector times matrix===
Similarly, a vector formula_5 of length formula_6 can be viewed as a row vector, corresponding to a formula_19 matrix. To make it clear that a row vector is meant, it is customary in this context to represent it as the transpose of a column vector; thus, one will see notations such as formula_20 The identity formula_21 holds. In index notation, if formula_10 is an formula_23 matrix, formula_24 amounts to:
